<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,737,762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tergite 
<number box="[371,385,737,761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
with 
<number box="[455,469,737,761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
short processes at posterior margin. Epandrial lobe long, thin, finger-like; surstylus rather thick with acute tip. Fore femur with long av (slightly longer than femur thickness).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="60" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,409,809,834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Description. Male</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[566,703,809,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.6">2.6–2.8 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[852,990,809,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.3 mm</quantity>
. Head black with pale gray pollen. Eyes very narrowly separated on face, brownish. Setae and setulae on head black except posteroventral surface with pale setulae; ocellar tubercle distinct with pair of long oc. Antenna black; first flagellomere long conical, 
<number box="[1332,1414,881,905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.65" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.7</number>
X longer than wide; arista very long, 2.0– 
<number box="[593,626,917,941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.1">2.1</number>
X length of first flagellomere; arista very short micropubescent. Proboscis long, 
<number box="[253,351,953,977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="0.725" valueMax="0.75" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.75</number>
X as long as head height, blackish to black with pale setulae. Palpus black with pale setulae (
<number box="[1392,1436,953,977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
apical setulae long).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
Thorax black with pale grey pollen. Setae and setulae on thorax black; pronotum with 
<number box="[1187,1201,1025,1049]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
seta laterally; 
<number box="[1370,1384,1025,1049]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
h, 
<number box="[1422,1436,1025,1049]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
npl, 
<number box="[202,243,1061,1085]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
short acr, 
<number box="[364,378,1061,1085]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="4.0">4</number>
dc, 
<number box="[427,441,1061,1085]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
psa; scutellum with 
<number box="[677,691,1061,1085]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
setae. Legs black except tips of all femora dark brownish yellow. Setulae and setae on legs black except those on coxae pale; fore femur basally with row of 
<number box="[1174,1188,1097,1121]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="5.0">5</number>
pale av setae (longest setae slightly longer than femur thickness), mid and hind femora with short pale av setulae. Fore femur 
<number box="[1348,1381,1133,1157]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as thick as mid femur, mid and hind femora subequal in thickness. Wing hyaline, slightly tinged grayish; veins dark brown. Squama dark yellow, bordered with pale setulae. Halter dark yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
Abdomen black with pale gray pollen. Setulae and setae on abdomen pale. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1323,1241,1265]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1589,1612]" captionTargetBox="[226,1348,240,1526]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[182,1404,190,1568]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Heleodromia (Heleodromia) didyma sp. nov. (male). 1. Tergite 8, dorsal view. 2. Genitalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: epl = epandrial lobe; epn = epandrium; hp = hypoproct process; hyp = hypandrium; ph = phallus; sur = surstylus; s 8 = sternite 8; t 8 = tergite 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
Figs. 
<number box="[1278,1323,1241,1265]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
): tergite 
<number box="[1421,1435,1241,1265]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
and sternite 
<number box="[300,314,1277,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
rather small; tergite 
<number box="[572,586,1277,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
narrowed posteriorly, with pair of short processes at posterior margin. Epandrium and hypandrium much elongated and rather large; epandrium shorter than hypandrium in lateral view; epandrial lobe long, thin, finger-like; surstylus rather thick with acute tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,284,1386,1410]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[444,533,1385,1409]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[687,777,1385,1409]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, but palpus with strong blackish setae, all femora with short pale av.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
