</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1054,1565,1589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" box="[197,1054,1565,1589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,1565,1589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to two marginal processes on tergite 
<number box="[1032,1048,1565,1589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,737,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1602,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Saigusa" authorityName="Saigusa" box="[805,1371,1601,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Heleodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreoalpina" subGenus="Heleodromia">
<emphasis box="[805,952,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Heleodromia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[971,1118,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Heleodromia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1138,1274,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">boreoalpina</emphasis>
Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1638,1661]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Japan</collectingCountry>
, but can be easily separated from it by the tips of all femora being dark brownish yellow, the fore femur basally with one row of 
<number box="[425,439,1673,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="5.0">5</number>
long pale av setae (longest setae slightly longer than femur thickness), and the surstylus with the acutely pointed tip. In 
<taxonomicName box="[503,965,1709,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Heleodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreoalpina" subGenus="Heleodromia">
<emphasis box="[503,650,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Heleodromia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[666,813,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Heleodromia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[829,965,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">boreoalpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the legs are entirely blackish, the femora lack prominent av setulae, and the surstylus is somewhat obtuse at tip (
<bibRefCitation author="Saigusa" box="[945,1100,1745,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" refString="Saigusa, T. (1963) Studies on the genus Heleodromia in Japan (Diptera, Empididae). Sieboldia, 3 (1), 119 - 130." type="journal article" year="1963">
Saigusa 
<number box="[1040,1100,1745,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
